reviews.text: I‚Äôm one the new tenants in the shopping center , Jax Mortgage Loans - Suite 11, help buyers with bad credit become mortgage ready for the mortgage loan process.  Burger and sliders were good. I will be hosting events here with Realtors for sure as a Mortgage Broker Business and Disabled Veteran Owned Business.

Best neighborhood bar in town! The food is great and inline with American cuisine but they also some southern comfort food mixed in with creative specials. The atmosphere is fun with whatever sporting events are currently taking place. Lillian‚Äôs also has some additional events going on most nights of the week, including bingo, trivia, open mic and live music from popular local bands. They even have a game room for the kids. Overall I can speak highly enough of them.

I always totally enjoy coming into Lillian‚Äôs for the delicious food wonderful service beverages and the awesome atmosphere. I tell people all the time I have never had a bad meal there. Tonite while sitting at the front bar I was able to convince a couple to check out the back bar and enjoy the music. After checking it out they immediately switched/moved to the back bar area and thanked me for letting them know. :-)

I'd heard ownership had changed, so I decided to give them another try and have been back three times.

Food: üëçüëçüëç good portions and flavor. The Ahi tuna app has always been a favorite. *Please being back the garlic cheese grits to go with it!* The nachos are also a solid choice. Great apps for beer drinking, lots of yummy entree options on the revamped menu. There has been a hiccup from the kitchen with our orders each visit but nothing worth sending back.

Atmosphere: Not a big fan of sports bars but this is a bit lower than your average noise level for a sports bar, not too bad. On my last visit while waiting and waiting for service, Barbie girl played loudly on repeat for quite a while which was a tad maddening  and started to leave when we were finally greeted.

Service: üëéüëéüëé NOT the place to go if you have a time limit or are starving! Takes a while to be greeted each time - somewhat understandable without a host and divided seating. Drinks can take 15 minutes to arrive, you're told they'll be right back to take the order you're ready to put in... ü¶ó ü¶ó ü¶ó
The check and boxes also come with an extended wait.

Hope to see improvements in future. Maybe I'll try take out next round...

The wings are delicious! I first tried on door dash and wanted to go in person and I can‚Äôt stop thinking about them lol the blue cheese is probably the best blue cheese I have ever had. I bought a container of it to keep at home üòÇ it‚Äôs a dive bar so nothing fancy which I prefer. The service is great. Our server was so kind and she let me try the clam chowder and it was so yummy. I will definitely get it next time. My hubby got the loaded hotdog and thought it was great. I saw they have daily specials which is nice! I am glad I found this place!

detailedReviews.author: Francine Zabawa
detailedReviews.text: Surprisingly a really good restaurant. It was pretty crowded when we went there but we got seated in the bar area right away. Our server was excellent and the good was terrific. Hubby had a really decent burger and I got the prime rib au jus sandwich; the roll was to die for! Soft inside and this incredible, chewey and well-finished crust, Jersey style. They had a big back room with a bar and a pretty good acoustic set going when we were there. The only reason I gave the atmosphere a 4 was cause the music in the bar dining area was way too loud, for me anyway. But we'll definitely be back!

detailedReviews.text: Our family has been meeting there for years. The 12 of us were meeting where the band is. We ordered appetizers and drinks until the rest of our family arrived. When they arrived an hour later the band was so horribly loud we had to move to the front of the restaurant.  We paid our bill and tipped our waitress generously.  When we got settled at oir table we were approached by the manager and was told we are cut off from ordering drinks!! Our bar tab was $100.00 for drinks and 4 appetizers for 10 people. We had a pitcher of beer and 2 of us had 2 drinks. And we were cut off ar 9:00 pm!  We will never go there again and we are telling everyone we know about our experience.
